						<summary>

						<p>On three slabs built into the floor of the big <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Agastyēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Śrīraṅga I, 1575 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Yuva, Kārtika ba. 30, Thursday.</hi> The details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1575 A.D., November 2,</hi> which was a <hi rend="bold">Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is much damaged and seems to refer to a money income of 12 <hi rend="italic">varāhas</hi> to god Agastyēśvara of Kommūru for maintaining the daily offerings.</p>						

						</summary>
